[h1]Lead Sight Revamped[/h1]
Updated and rebranded for current Avorion versions.
Original Mod: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2538356784

[i]All core concept and design credit goes to [url=https://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561198196116626]SigmatroN[/url], the original creator of Lead Sight. Following a multi-year hiatus, this revamped version is an officially maintained continuation focused on compatibility, stability, and long-term support.[/i]

[hr][/hr]

[u][b]What does this mod do?[/b][/u]
Lead Sight Revamped provides predictive gun sights for projectile weapons, taking shooter and target velocities into account to help you land shots on moving targets more reliably. 

Enjoy firing your machine guns, cannons, and bolters, but struggle to lead targets? Then this is the mod for you! No more misses. Just aim at the reticle and shoot!

[u][b]Features:[/b][/u]
[quote][list]
[*]Predictive lead reticle for your selected target.[/*]
[*]Quick toggle with the [b]/[/b] key (slash) accompanied by an audible feedback sound so you know it switched.[/*]
[*]Range-based reticle colors for readability:
  [list]
  [*][b]Red[/b] = Out of reach[/*]
  [*][b]Yellow/Orange[/b] = Partial reach (some weapons can connect)[/*]
  [*][b]Green[/b] = Favorable reach window[/*]
  [/list][/*]
[*]Lead calculation is based on average projectile turret behavior and relative movement (lasers/seekers do not count).[/*]
[*]Keeps the classic feel of the original mod while improving reliability on modern Avorion versions.[/*]
[/list][/quote]

[u][b]Revamped Stability Improvements:[/b][/u]
[quote][list]
[*]Additional defensive checks to reduce edge-case script failures.[/*]
[*]Integrated the critical no-buzz/no-crash laser audio hotfix provided by SigmatroN.[/*]
[*]Cleaner effect handling to reduce stale reticle artifacts during gameplay transitions.[/*]
[*]Chat toggle messages disabled by default to avoid unrelated “You’re not in a group” spam; audio cue remains active.[/*]
[/list][/quote]

[u][b]Known issues / limitations:[/b][/u]
[quote][list]
[*]The reticle can appear hidden behind objects since it is a world-space 3D effect, not a screen-space UI element.[/*]
[*]Weapon aggregation behavior is constrained by the game API; all projectile weapons are taken into account when calculating, even in inactive weapon groups.[/*]
[/list][/quote]

[u][b]Development Status (May 2026):[/b][/u]
[i]Yes, it works![/i] Actively tested on current builds with stability updates applied. Current release focus is solid functionality first, followed by optional UX enhancements (including improved chat feedback handling).

